==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heteropoda
<hw>Het`e*rop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ other + <ets>-poda</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
order of pelagic Gastropoda, having the foot developed into a median
fin. Some of the species are naked; others, as <gen>Carinaria</gen> and
<gen>Atlanta</gen>, have thin glassy shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heteropodous</ent>⟦br⟧
